            "text_UxP86R": {
              "type": "text",
              "settings": {
                "text": "<p>The Collection Recognisable forms. One-off finishes. Every Neuthread garment is made from reclaimed textiles, which means each piece carries its own variation in texture, tone and character. The design stays true. The fabric makes it unique. No excess. No exact repeats. Just design-led fashion made differently. CTA: View all pieces Brand proposition Fashion, rethought. Neuthread creates distinctive garments from reclaimed materials, bringing together strong design, skilled making and a more thoughtful way of producing fashion. Same design. Different fabric. Our garments follow fixed patterns, but the materials change every time. That means the silhouette remains recognisable while the finish, texture and detail are always unique. The result is consistency without sameness. Structure without repetition. Difference by design Powered by difference. Neuthread is shaped by neurodiverse creativity. Different perspectives are not a side note to the brand. They are part of its creative engine — influencing how materials are seen, how design decisions are made, and how overlooked things are turned into something valuable. Difference here is not something added on. It is built in. This shouldn't exist. Most fashion begins with something new. Neuthread begins with what already exists. We take reclaimed textiles and transform them into garments designed to be worn, kept and remembered. Not despite their past, but because of it. Limited by material, not demand. We do not produce in volume. Every release is shaped by the textiles available, which means quantities stay small and outcomes stay distinctive. When the fabric changes, the garment changes. When it runs out, the piece ends there. That is how we keep production controlled, reduce waste, and protect what makes Neuthread special. Daisy Chain / wider impact Part of something wider. Neuthread is part of Daisy Chain and rooted in the North East. The brand creates space for neurodiverse creativity within design and making, while supporting wider work with autistic and neurodivergent people and families across the region. This is not separate from the clothes. It is part of the same belief: that overlooked materials and overlooked perspectives can create something extraordinary. Closing CTA Designed differently. Made deliberately. Worn with purpose. Shop the current collection or join us as Neuthread continues to grow. CTA: Shop now Secondary CTA: Learn more</p>",
                "width": "fit-content",
                "max_width": "narrow",
                "alignment": "left",
                "type_preset": "custom",
                "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
                "font_size": "1rem",
                "line_height": "normal",
